  <h1>BRIEF HISTORY OF MSSN IN NIGERIA</h1>
  <p>MSSN was founded in Lagos, Nigeria on 18th April 1954, in response to the yearnings of Muslim students for a platform to discuss and find solutions to problems and challenges. Especially in the face of hostile colonial and evangelical environment, then prevalent in the country. The organization has since then continued to adapt and respond to the changing challenges and needs of its members in particular and the Muslim in general.
The founders and initiators were Muslims students in notable secondary schools in Lagos which include: Prof. Kareem Hussein of LUTH, Lateef Adegbite, Abdurrahaman Sahid, Babs Fafunwa, Tajudeen Aromashodun and others. MSSN has since grown in leaps and bounds to be the largest religious organization or otherwise in west Africa with millions as members. Membership is drawn from all primary and post primary institution in Nigeria and has branches, area branches and central branches which are also created to accommodate those who have left school but are still desirous of remaining within the fold of MSS. The contribution of MSS to national development is enormous. MSS serves as a patent tool of national unity and cohesion, apart from its membership that cuts across geographical and ethnic barriers.
MSSN is promoting national integration and enlightening people through its programmes and activities that emphasizes the brotherhood of Islam in particular and mankind in general, furthermore, the society has continued to produce generations of outstanding leaders in all spheres of national life. (Educationist, Professors, Entrepreneurs, public service holders etc). also defining and encouraging adherence to certain minimum standards of national ethics. The society has remained a pressure group and striving for the advancement of the interest of Islam.
Indeed, past members of MSS occupies leadership position of virtually all leading Islamic organization in Nigeria.
MSS achievements transcends boundaries of Nigeria. It played lead roles in the formation of international student Organization such as International Islamic Federation of Students Organisation (IIFSO) based in Saudi Arabia, the International Institute of Islamic Thought (IIIT) with headquarters in United States serves as an inspiration to the information of others in different parts of the world, including Muslim Students Association (MSA) of Canada and America. The society is affiliated to many local and international organizations whose aims and objectives are in consonance with its. MSSN and its constitution are registered with appropriate organs of the government of the federation of Nigeria.
</p> 
  <h2>Objectives of MSSN</h2>
  <p>Its major objective is to be a forum for making every Muslim youth that is privileged to attend any school in the country, secondary or tertiary, to be conscious about Islam and to be one its good ambassadors. </p>
  <h2>Impacts of MSSN</h2>
  <p> In the last 60 years of its existence, its greatest achievement is in anyone who, after passing through the walls of formal educational settings, still takes pride in Islam. Aside from this, MSSN has produced Muslim elites, professionals, politicians, academics and business giants who today are vanguards of Islam. It has also produced great Islamic scholars and da’wah workers whose indelible mark in da’wah efforts in this country cannot be erased, even by time.</p>
